<p align="center">
	###</p>
<p align="center">
	<em>Carl Deal and Tia Lessin are Academy Award&reg; nominated filmmakers who also produced and directed TROUBLE THE WATER, winner of the Gotham Independent Film Award, the Sundance Film Festival&rsquo;s Grand Jury Prize, and the Full Frame Documentary Festival Grand Jury Prize. Deal and Lessin were, respectively, archival and supervising producers of Michael Moore&rsquo;s FAHRENHEIT 9/11, winner of the Palm d&rsquo;Or, Academy Award&reg;-winning BOWLING FOR COLUMBINE and co-producers of his most recent film CAPITALISM: A LOVE STORY.</em></p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>

    
